  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Background: The main goal when diagnosing thyroid nodules, is to differentiate the few
      malignant from the overwhelming background of benign nodules. Currently available
      pre-operative tests are unable to rule out malignancy in a subset of patients and diagnostic
      thyroid surgery is necessary. Therefore, there is a need to develope the diagnostic tools for
      pre-operative diagnostic work-up of thyroid nodules.

      The study will investigate a novel ultrasonographic technique called Shear Wave Elastography
      (SWE) in the pre-operative evaluation of thyroid nodules.

      Aim:

      To evaluate the diagnostic value of SWE in the pre-operative diagnosis of thyroid nodules in
      a tertiary surgical center.

      Perspectives:

      An optimization of the pre-operative risk-stratification and diagnosis of thyroid nodules can
      reduce unnecessary thyroid surgery, with a reduction in morbidity and better use of the
      economic and surgical resources.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
